body_html:
@amrit-poudel Thanks for the clear description of the problem!

The error message indicates that sparse_tensor_to_dense doesn't support complex values yet; we simply haven't implemented it. Calling sess.run on a complex dense tensor works, since it doesn't involve sparse_tensor_to_dense.

@concretevitamin might know whether we have any plans to add support for complex values to sparse_tensor_to_dense.
